    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nWhen using \"set number\" to display line numbers and vertically split the window in diff mode, setting the width of the left window to 1 causes display distortion when scrolling.\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\nnvim --clean\r\n`:set number`\r\n`:set termguicolors`\r\n`:hi WinSeparator guibg=red`\r\n`:hi FoldColumn   guibg=blue`\r\n`100Oa<ESC>`\r\n`gg`\r\n`:vs`\r\n`:difft`\r\n`<C-w>l`\r\n`:difft`\r\n`<C-w>|`\r\n`<C-f>`\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/12369962/7735e0b0-dc4a-4c4f-8a0b-02b45f969905)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nIn nvim 0.9.5, the display does not become distorted.\r\n![image](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/12369962/32fd6753-f220-4821-adb7-fe5d775d5f9d)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\r\n\r\nNVIM v0.11.0-dev-108+g22fe04452\r\n\r\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\r\n\r\nno, vim 9.1\r\n\r\n### Operating system/version\r\n\r\nUbuntu 24.04\r\n\r\n### Terminal name/version\r\n\r\nGNOME Terminal 3.52.0 using VTE 0.76.0 +BIDI +GNUTLS +ICU +SYSTEMD\r\n\r\n### $TERM environment variable\r\n\r\nxterm-256color\r\n\r\n### Installation\r\n\r\nbuild from repo",
